paradox : the ability to understand that more than one thing is true at a time
i am consciously deciding to not know
soon or later, everyone invents a story which they believe to be their life

the idea of having many selves or no self at all - the self illusion - is fascinating. the virtual self being more commonly shallow but key in today’s world, people have reached this understanding now of how they individually can manipulate their social media image to create their own ideal persona, knowing approximately which post will generate which reaction (numbers of like, numbers of comment). a second layer of understanding is that some of them are even aware of the consequences a post will have on themselves : instant gratification. so if you know that the more skin you reveal, the more likes you get, you should also observe your confidence level before and after posting, the impact of the number of likes on your self-esteem and how long does the impact last. there are many other ways of getting the satisfaction of validation. an efficient one is to not look for validation, lower your expectations. the only validation that should matter to you and affect you the most is your own, and the one from the ones you trust, worship and admire with reciprocity.

if we were to remember with clarity, how hard would it be to differentiate the now and the past. if i were to control my experience of life to a greater extent - if my own perception of how things happen became the only narrative, would that mean i would be getting away from other people's experiences.. would we all be living in parallel worlds
what are we gonna do with all this future
